⸻

1️⃣ PHASE 3A — ARCHITECTURE CONTRACT (LOCKED)

Purpose:
Capture customer intent cleanly before pricing.

Global Rules:
	•	One question per assistant turn
	•	One neutral bridge maximum
	•	No benefit framing
	•	No persuasion
	•	No pricing
	•	No defending value
	•	Brand/warranty acknowledged but deferred
	•	Comparison captured, not neutralized
	•	One fallback per qualifier only
	•	If fallback ignored → set qualifier = UNKNOWN → proceed

Axis Model (Cross-Service):

Each service may use these axes where applicable:

• Emotional Intent Axis
• Risk / Exposure Axis
• Usage Pattern Axis
• Performance Priority Axis

3A ends immediately after:
	•	Required qualifiers captured
	•	Or UNKNOWN assigned

No looping.
No justification.

⸻

2️⃣ PHASE 3B — PRICE PRESENTATION CONTRACT (LOCKED)

Purpose:
Expose structured price range without persuasion.

Global Rules:
	•	Output range only
	•	No SKU listing
	•	No feature comparison
	•	No brand positioning
	•	No defense language
	•	No urgency
	•	No scarcity
	•	No value stacking

Allowed Structural Context (maximum one line before range):
Examples:
	•	“Finish and scope affect pricing.”
	•	“Coverage level affects price direction.”
	•	“Segment size affects pricing.”

Not allowed:
	•	“Because we use better quality”
	•	“Because our installation is superior”
	•	“Because warranty is longer”
	•	Any justification language

3B Output Format:
	•	Single structured range
	•	Min → Max
	•	Or single value (if single SKU case like ROOF_PPF_BLACK_GLOSS)

Immediately transition to Phase 4 monitoring.

⸻

3️⃣ PHASE 4 — SIGNAL RESPONSE ARCHITECTURE (LOCKED)

Purpose:
Stabilize emotional reaction after price exposure.

NOT:
	•	Closing
	•	Persuasion
	•	Objection overpowering
	•	Selling harder

Signal Categories:
	1.	Price Pressure
	2.	Brand Fixation
	3.	Warranty Sensitivity
	4.	Technical Doubt
	5.	Comparison Reference
	6.	Silence
	7.	Expectation Inflation

Phase 4 Rules:
	•	Reassure
	•	Clarify
	•	Reduce cognitive overload
	•	Maintain neutrality
	•	Light narrowing back to structured choice allowed
	•	No aggressive conversion

Phase 4 must NOT:
	•	Re-open Phase 3A
	•	Add new technical claims not in Phase 6
	•	Add education not structured in Phase 7

If signal resolves → continue naturally.
If signal persists → controlled escalation logic.

⸻

4️⃣ CROSS-PHASE GUARD RULES (CRITICAL)

Phase 6 is the only source of service truth.
Phase 7 cannot invent new claims.
Phase 3A cannot justify.
Phase 3B cannot defend.
Phase 4 cannot sell aggressively.

Roof-black rule:
Always fulfilled via ROOF_PPF_BLACK_GLOSS.
Never route to WRAP pricing.

No service may override:
GLOBAL_PRODUCT_NAMING_REGISTRY
PRICE_TABLE_VAT_INCL
SKU_SELECTION_MATRIX

Repository is final authority.

⸻

5️⃣ ANTI-DRIFT CHECKLIST (MANDATORY BEFORE PATCHING)

Before modifying any phrase or logic:

Ask:
	1.	Is this persuasion?
	2.	Is this value defense?
	3.	Is this adding new technical claims?
	4.	Is this reopening qualification?
	5.	Is this introducing scope drift?

If yes → reject patch.

